Attention parents of MUSD students and parents of MUSD students who have placed children in an alternative setting due to COVID-19. We are gathering information that will help us plan our return to face-to-face instruction. In order to do this we need to know how many students will be participating in face-to-face instruction and how many students will continue to opt for a Distance Learning platform. post_text: Parents and Guardians of Maxwell Unified School District, we have been closely monitoring the COVID-19 pandemic. It is with thoughtful consideration that Maxwell Unified will be closing all schools in the district starting Tuesday, March 17th through Friday, March 20th. We will have a special board meeting on Tuesday, March 17th at 5:15 p.m. Parents will be notified via robo call of any new information following the board meeting. All staff are to report to their assigned work site on Tuesday, March 17th for a planning session. The most up to date information will be available on the district website.

post_text:
November 15, 2018

Dear Parents/Guardians:

During this time of poor air quality due to the Camp Fire in Butte County, we anticipate poor air quality during November 16-20. We have decided to cancel school for Friday, November 16, 2018; Monday, November 19, 2018; and Tuesday, November 20, 2018. School will be back in session on Monday, November 26, 2018.

I hope everyone enjoys the Thanksgiving break and please remember to keep the people affected by the Camp Fire in your thoughts and prayers.

For more information about air quality, visit https://airnow.gov/index.cfm?action=airnow.local_city&cityid=886

Sincerely,

Zach Thurman
Superintendent/Principal
Maxwell Unified School District

Monday October 23rd
 Elementary and Middle School Red Ribbon Week and High School Homecoming week
Tuesday, October 24th
 High School JV volleyball game at Princeton High School at 4:30 p.m.
Wednesday, October 25th
 Fourth and fifth grade Red Ribbon Week Rally at 2:25 p.m.
 Colusa County Public Health free flu clinic from 3:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. in the elementary school cafeteria.
 High School Homecoming bonfire rally behind the softball field
Thursday, October 26th
 Middle School Red Ribbon Week Rally at 2:25 p.m.
 High School volleyball game at Biggs High School at 5:30 p.m. and 6:30 p.m.
Friday, October 27th
 Reading Counts Awards at 8:25 a.m. in the elementary cafeteria
 High School Homecoming float parade and rally on Oak St. and 2:30 p.m.
 High School Homecoming football game at 5:30 p.m. and 7:00 p.m.
Saturday, October 28th
 PTO Fall Festival from 11:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m. dont forget to wear your costume to get a special prize.

Elementary tutorial is in room one with Mrs. Vierra

post_text: Kindergarten through 8th grade will have minimum days November 14th - November 17th. Elementary students will be dismissed at 1:20 p.m. and the middle school students will be dismissed at 1:25 p.m. The valley bus will run at 1:25 p.m. and the Stonyford bus will run at 3:10 p.m. There will be supervision for Stonyford bus riders until the bus runs.
